        "width": 500,
        "height": 30
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Members of the Fredericksburg Artillery held a reenactment of a Confederate encampment June 23 at Auburn (Neavil's) Mill near Casanova as part of an open house celebration hosted by Earth Design Associates.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 1250,
        "width": 500,
        "height": 60
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The mill, renovated during the past few years by Earth Design, was open to visitors throughout the day. Barry W. Starke hosted the event.",
